What you need to know:

The round-robin tournament will be played as Women’s Twenty20 Internationals. Only the winner will join already qualified England, Australia, India, New Zealand, South Africa, Pakistan and Barbados at the 2022 Commonwealth Games slated for July 29 to August 7 in Birmingham.Kenya won the annual Kwibuka T20 tournament in June 2021 in Kigali, Rwanda where Wetoto and Abel emerged the best bowler and batter respectively. Abel was also the Best Player of the tournament in Kigali. 